==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spume
<hw>Spume</hw> <pr>(sp⟦umac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>spuma</ets>. Cf. <er>Pumice</er>, <er>Spoom</er>.]</ety>
<def>Frothy matter raised on liquids by boiling, effervescence, or
agitation; froth; foam; scum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Materials dark and crude,⟦br⟧
Of spiritous and fiery <qex>spume</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spume</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spume
<hw>Spume</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Spumed</conjf> <pr>(sp⟦umac⟧md)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Spuming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>spumare</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To froth; to foam.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spumeous</ent>⟦br⟧
